WEBVTT

00:06.006 --> 00:08.592
[somber music]

00:08.592 --> 00:11.429
[Filip] She wanted to die.
She didn't have to kill Cyn.

00:11.429 --> 00:13.848
She didn't kill him.
You did.

00:13.848 --> 00:15.391
[Clarissa] Have you heard
of Winnipesaukee Island?

00:15.391 --> 00:17.768
Islands are private enclaves
for wealthy people,

00:17.768 --> 00:19.854
and each has a hangar
with a suborbital shuttle.

00:19.854 --> 00:20.938
That'll get us to Luna.

00:20.938 --> 00:22.064
We have put together

00:22.064 --> 00:23.733
proportional response
strike packages.

00:23.733 --> 00:26.610
Pallas Station is the one
I think we should focus on.

00:26.610 --> 00:28.362
If we start murdering
innocent Belters,

00:28.362 --> 00:31.157
we'll be fighting
the entire Belt.

00:31.157 --> 00:32.324
Speak your mind.

00:32.324 --> 00:33.492
I think we should
blow up Pallas Station.

00:33.492 --> 00:35.578
[Naomi]
My name is Naomi Nagata,

00:35.578 --> 00:37.747
and I'm aboard the freighter
Chetzemoka.

00:37.747 --> 00:40.499
An automated distress call
in my voice

00:40.499 --> 00:42.543
is being broadcast
from this ship.

00:42.543 --> 00:43.627
[Naomi over recording]
If you get this message,

00:43.627 --> 00:44.712
please retransmit.

00:44.712 --> 00:46.672
[Naomi]
It is a lie, a simulation

00:46.672 --> 00:48.883
to lure the Rocinante
into a trap.

00:48.883 --> 00:50.926
The Chetzemoka is a bomb.

00:50.926 --> 00:52.052
[Karal]
The truth is,

00:52.052 --> 00:53.804
Naomi Nagata was
a traitor to the Belt,

00:53.804 --> 00:55.473
- and now she dead.
- Pashángimang!

00:55.473 --> 00:57.933
Camina!
[whispering] Please..

00:57.933 --> 01:00.978
[crying] If you get this
message, please retransmit.

01:00.978 --> 01:02.271
Tell James...

01:02.271 --> 01:04.815
[Naomi over recording]
Holden I am in...

01:04.815 --> 01:07.067
- control.
- Why did the message change?

01:07.067 --> 01:08.277
[Naomi over recording]
Naomi Nagata...

01:08.277 --> 01:09.820
Could someone be
on the ship?

01:09.820 --> 01:11.989
- Could it be Naomi?
- It's impossible.

01:13.282 --> 01:14.116
[Naomi over recording]
...control.

01:14.116 --> 01:15.659
She's dead.

01:20.956 --> 01:22.416
[Pella crewman]
Five Golden Bough raiders

01:22.416 --> 01:25.169
engaged two UNN cruisers
and one MCRN heavy frigate

01:25.169 --> 01:26.837
near Patroclus.

01:26.837 --> 01:29.340
Four Golden Bough killed.
One UNN cruiser destroyed.

01:29.340 --> 01:30.966
The other withdraw.

01:30.966 --> 01:32.802
And the Martian frigate
was reported lost.

01:32.802 --> 01:34.637
The Free Navy
mourns our allies

01:34.637 --> 01:36.680
who died
in this valiant effort.

01:38.307 --> 01:40.643
But it was worth the price.

01:44.814 --> 01:47.149
Captain, tight-beam
come in for you

01:47.149 --> 01:49.235
from Dewalt.

01:49.235 --> 01:51.779
Send it here.

01:51.779 --> 01:54.573
[Karal] Bosmang, as ordered,
we have been monitoring

01:54.573 --> 01:56.700
the Chetzemoka,

01:56.700 --> 01:59.662
and now
maybe there is a problem.

01:59.662 --> 02:02.122
The distress call you created,
it stop,

02:02.122 --> 02:05.876
and before it stop,
it change to this...

02:05.876 --> 02:07.837
[Naomi over recording] This is
Naomi Nagata of the Roc...

02:07.837 --> 02:09.964
[click]

02:09.964 --> 02:11.841
Tell James Holden I am in...
[click]

02:11.841 --> 02:13.634
This is Naomi Nagata
of the Roc...

02:13.634 --> 02:15.427
[click]

02:15.427 --> 02:17.054
Tell James Holden
I am in...

02:17.054 --> 02:18.889
[click]

02:18.889 --> 02:20.975
...control.

02:20.975 --> 02:22.601
This is Naomi Nagata
of the Roc...

02:22.601 --> 02:23.936
[click]

02:23.936 --> 02:25.479
Tell James Holden I...

02:25.479 --> 02:27.189
[click]
This is Naomi Nagata

02:27.189 --> 02:30.067
of the Roc...
[click]

02:30.067 --> 02:31.652
Tell James Holden I am in...
[click]

02:31.652 --> 02:33.445
So, when we first
picked this up,

02:33.445 --> 02:36.323
the distress call said she had
no control and nav.

02:36.323 --> 02:38.617
Now some random comm
malfunction

02:38.617 --> 02:41.328
just happens to turn that into
"I am in control"

02:41.328 --> 02:44.039
- four times in a row?
- ...control.

02:44.039 --> 02:45.958
That really seem random
to you?

02:45.958 --> 02:47.501
This is Naomi Nagata.

02:49.962 --> 02:51.881
Tell James Holden I am in...
[click]

02:53.757 --> 02:55.634
...control.

02:55.634 --> 02:57.428
It could be a malfunction.

02:57.428 --> 02:58.971
Comms start to fail,

02:58.971 --> 03:00.556
transmitter
begins dropping out.

03:00.556 --> 03:02.683
Finally,
everything just goes dead.

03:04.310 --> 03:06.896
Sorry. That's a bad
choice of words.

03:06.896 --> 03:09.690
Maybe she's not in a position
to speak freely,

03:09.690 --> 03:12.401
or she's hurt, and she
can't get to a microphone.

03:12.401 --> 03:14.904
Or she doesn't have
full access to comms.

03:14.904 --> 03:17.948
There's no way to know
until we get there.

03:17.948 --> 03:20.951
Well, we're a lot closer
than the Roci.

03:20.951 --> 03:22.202
We'll get there first.

03:22.202 --> 03:24.622
If it is intentional,
why be so cryptic?

03:24.622 --> 03:26.832
Why not just come out
and say what's going on?

03:26.832 --> 03:29.209
All we can do is get there
as fast as we can.

03:29.209 --> 03:31.503
[Bull] We don't exactly
have fuel to waste.

03:33.964 --> 03:36.842
But I'll see if we can
increase our burn.

03:36.842 --> 03:39.845
[dramatic music]

03:39.845 --> 03:43.223
♪ ♪

03:43.223 --> 03:45.392
This is Naomi Nagata...
[click]

03:47.561 --> 03:49.313
Tell James Holden
I am in...

03:49.313 --> 03:50.940
[click]

03:50.940 --> 03:52.650
...control.

03:58.405 --> 04:00.908
[Naomi gasping for air]

04:00.908 --> 04:03.953
[beeping]

04:03.953 --> 04:06.372
[breathing heavily]

04:07.915 --> 04:10.501
[beeping increases rapidly]

04:10.501 --> 04:13.671
[wheezing]

04:13.671 --> 04:17.549
[rapid beeping continues]

04:17.549 --> 04:19.051
[gasps]

04:19.051 --> 04:21.637
[wheezing]

04:26.809 --> 04:29.979
[groaning]

04:29.979 --> 04:32.022
[grunts angrily]

04:35.901 --> 04:38.737
[slurping]

05:00.175 --> 05:03.512
[quiet music]

05:03.512 --> 05:10.519
♪ ♪

05:14.565 --> 05:17.901
[music intensifies]

05:17.901 --> 05:20.112
♪ ♪

05:20.112 --> 05:23.115
[pensive instrumental music]

05:23.115 --> 05:30.080
♪ ♪

05:38.380 --> 05:41.508
[woman singing in Norwegian]

05:41.508 --> 05:47.222
♪ ♪

06:06.533 --> 06:13.373
♪ ♪

06:30.099 --> 06:33.102
[tentative music]

06:33.102 --> 06:40.109
♪ ♪

07:13.934 --> 07:16.937
[sweeping orchestration]

07:16.937 --> 07:23.944
♪ ♪

07:32.119 --> 07:35.247
[blades thrumming]

07:46.717 --> 07:50.179
[soft footsteps]

08:06.195 --> 08:09.072
[Erich, whispering]
How do we get into the hangar?

08:09.072 --> 08:11.950
[Amos] I think I see it.
Stay behind me.

08:23.337 --> 08:26.340
[uneasy music]

08:26.340 --> 08:33.347
♪ ♪

09:07.256 --> 09:10.509
[metal rumbles, squeals]

09:10.509 --> 09:17.516
♪ ♪

09:17.516 --> 09:20.269
[Erich] You really know
how to fly one of these?

09:20.269 --> 09:22.980
I do.

09:22.980 --> 09:29.987
♪ ♪

09:29.987 --> 09:31.113
[clatter, guns cock]

09:31.113 --> 09:32.322
[porter]
Don't shoot!

09:32.322 --> 09:34.283
Don't shoot.

09:34.283 --> 09:36.994
Anything that's worth money's
in the house.

09:36.994 --> 09:38.578
- Just take what you want.
[Hutch] Thanks.

09:38.578 --> 09:40.163
[Erich] You live here?
[maid] Y-yes.

09:40.163 --> 09:41.748
I mean in the house.

09:41.748 --> 09:42.916
We're the winter staff.

09:42.916 --> 09:44.584
Why are you guys
hiding in here?

09:44.584 --> 09:45.919
[cook] We saw
your helicopter landing.

09:45.919 --> 09:47.546
It wasn't marked U.N.

09:47.546 --> 09:48.880
We thought if you
were coming to steal,

09:48.880 --> 09:50.215
you'd go to the house.

09:50.215 --> 09:52.134
[Amos] Depends on what
we're here to steal.

09:52.134 --> 09:53.510
My name's Clarissa.

09:53.510 --> 09:55.929
My family had a house on
the other side of the island.

09:55.929 --> 09:57.431
[cook]
Clarissa Mao?

09:57.431 --> 09:59.433
Your family came
to Thanksgiving one year.

09:59.433 --> 10:01.977
- [softly] That's right.
[cook] You and your sister

10:01.977 --> 10:03.228
spent the entire time fighting.

10:03.228 --> 10:04.688
- And my mom made us...
[Erich] Hey!

10:04.688 --> 10:06.773
Who gives a fuck?
Business first.

10:06.773 --> 10:08.859
Tearful reunions later.

10:08.859 --> 10:10.902
Where's the family
that lived here?

10:10.902 --> 10:12.154
Uh, they left
a few months ago.

10:12.154 --> 10:14.114
What about this shuttle?
Is it lunar capable?

10:14.114 --> 10:16.241
Yeah, but the ship
hasn't flown in a while.

10:16.241 --> 10:18.618
Not since I started
working here two years ago.

10:18.618 --> 10:20.704
[porter] Some kind of problem
with the reactor, I think.

10:20.704 --> 10:22.664
[Hutch]
Fuck!

10:22.664 --> 10:24.791
[Erich]
Keep an eye on them.

10:29.087 --> 10:35.677
♪ ♪

10:35.677 --> 10:38.221
[hydraulics hiss]

10:38.221 --> 10:40.682
[Erich]
Oh, nice!

10:43.101 --> 10:45.228
Batteries still work.

10:45.228 --> 10:47.356
Batteries won't get us
into orbit.

10:47.356 --> 10:52.027
♪ ♪

11:04.956 --> 11:08.752
[soft background chatter]

11:14.132 --> 11:15.509
[ting]

11:19.888 --> 11:21.264
[chime]

11:29.231 --> 11:32.275
[commotion, applause]

11:32.275 --> 11:34.277
[overlapping chatter]

11:34.277 --> 11:35.695
[man]
Congratulations.

11:35.695 --> 11:37.989
[woman] That's right.
[man] That's right!

11:41.451 --> 11:43.328
You son of a bitch.

11:44.996 --> 11:47.666
Nice to see you, too.

11:47.666 --> 11:49.668
You went behind
my back.

11:49.668 --> 11:50.836
The Secretary-General

11:50.836 --> 11:52.963
asked me
for my professional opinion,

11:52.963 --> 11:54.548
and I gave it to him.

11:54.548 --> 11:57.050
[Clarke] Inaros was connected
to the arsenal on Callisto.

11:57.050 --> 11:58.885
Maybe that should be
on the table as well.

11:58.885 --> 12:00.720
[Tesfaye] Callisto
is a Martian facility.

12:00.720 --> 12:02.597
So what?

12:02.597 --> 12:04.975
If the Belters on Tycho
threw in with Inaros,

12:04.975 --> 12:07.561
I call that a legitimate
target, too...

12:07.561 --> 12:09.646
- Earth Corp or not.
[Avasarala] A target for what?

12:09.646 --> 12:10.814
Follow-up strikes.

12:10.814 --> 12:12.941
I'm expanding
the Pallas initiative.

12:12.941 --> 12:14.651
The only thing
we should be discussing

12:14.651 --> 12:15.944
is to how to spin this strike

12:15.944 --> 12:18.238
as a limited
military objective.

12:18.238 --> 12:21.241
And make it clear that we are
not at war with the Belt.

12:21.241 --> 12:23.368
We are at war
with the Belt.

12:23.368 --> 12:25.495
Madam, I respect
you feel differently, but...

12:25.495 --> 12:29.124
Inaros is an extremist,
a rogue element,

12:29.124 --> 12:32.210
as much of a danger
to his own people

12:32.210 --> 12:33.837
as he is to us.

12:33.837 --> 12:35.338
He didn't throw rocks
at Belters.

12:35.338 --> 12:38.216
And we cannot let him
frame this any other way.

12:38.216 --> 12:39.759
I understand
why you're upset.

12:39.759 --> 12:42.012
I should have told you about
Pallas when I made my decision.

12:42.012 --> 12:44.931
If we continue to attack
civilian targets...

12:44.931 --> 12:46.183
The way Inaros
did to us?

12:46.183 --> 12:48.518
Is he our role model now?

12:49.603 --> 12:52.189
No matter what
Marco Inaros claims,

12:52.189 --> 12:55.859
the Belters
are not one nation.

12:55.859 --> 12:57.569
We can exploit that.

12:57.569 --> 12:59.863
We can ally
with certain factions,

12:59.863 --> 13:01.656
enlist them in common cause.

13:01.656 --> 13:03.492
That kind of diplomacy
takes time

13:03.492 --> 13:04.993
which we can't afford
to waste.

13:04.993 --> 13:06.870
Our job...

13:06.870 --> 13:09.539
my job
is to make our people safer

13:09.539 --> 13:11.333
and to reduce the enemy's
ability to hurt us

13:11.333 --> 13:12.626
as quickly as possible.

13:12.626 --> 13:14.169
[Delgado]
We have to take this fight

13:14.169 --> 13:16.046
back to the bastards
who started it.

13:16.046 --> 13:18.256
And anyone else
who cheers them on.

13:18.256 --> 13:21.176
You think
I don't want that?

13:21.176 --> 13:23.845
You think I don't go
to sleep every night

13:23.845 --> 13:28.350
dreaming about putting
Marco Inaros on the hooks...

13:28.350 --> 13:30.352
watching him gasp for air...

13:30.352 --> 13:34.314
and making his children watch
him draw his final breath

13:34.314 --> 13:36.983
because
he murdered my husband?

13:36.983 --> 13:40.403
[somber music]

13:40.403 --> 13:42.822
♪ ♪

13:42.822 --> 13:45.534
My Arjun is dead,

13:45.534 --> 13:49.579
and I'd sacrifice everything
to bring him back.

13:49.579 --> 13:51.164
And right now

13:51.164 --> 13:54.251
everyone who loved
someone on Pallas

13:54.251 --> 13:57.754
is feeling what I feel.

13:57.754 --> 14:00.173
For every partisan we killed,

14:00.173 --> 14:02.634
we made ten more.

14:05.345 --> 14:07.973
[sighs softly]

14:07.973 --> 14:11.726
Madam, I am truly sorry
for your loss,

14:11.726 --> 14:15.063
but we can't let emotion
make these choices.

14:15.063 --> 14:17.607
We have to be rational
and objective.

14:17.607 --> 14:19.359
I think we should hit
Ceres Station.

14:19.359 --> 14:21.945
It's the biggest port
in the Belt.

14:21.945 --> 14:23.863
[Paster] I thought
Anderson Dawes was a friend.

14:23.863 --> 14:25.156
[Clarke]
He'd never oppose Inaros

14:25.156 --> 14:26.366
when push comes to shove.

14:26.366 --> 14:27.909
[Delgado]
With Ceres and Pallas denied,

14:27.909 --> 14:29.869
Inaros will be forced back
to the outer planets

14:29.869 --> 14:31.079
to resupply.

14:31.079 --> 14:33.582
It'll spread them thin.

14:33.582 --> 14:35.458
It's a bold move.

14:35.458 --> 14:37.002
There are millions
of people on Ceres,

14:37.002 --> 14:40.297
hundreds of thousands
of children.

14:40.297 --> 14:42.090
What are the scenarios

14:42.090 --> 14:43.550
for a full-scale attack?

14:43.550 --> 14:45.844
Is the intention
to incapacitate or occupy?

14:45.844 --> 14:48.096
I will not be a part of this.

14:50.015 --> 14:51.349
Are you stepping down?

14:51.349 --> 14:52.517
Yes, sir.

14:52.517 --> 14:55.562
Fine.
I accept your resignation.

14:55.562 --> 14:56.980
You're dismissed.

14:56.980 --> 15:00.483
[dramatic music]

15:00.483 --> 15:02.569
You'll have to accept mine
as well, sir.

15:02.569 --> 15:06.114
[Clarke]
Jesus. Dahane...

15:06.114 --> 15:07.407
[Cebotari]
And mine.

15:07.407 --> 15:10.660
[Yilmaz] We're supposed to be
better than this.

15:10.660 --> 15:16.666
♪ ♪

15:20.295 --> 15:23.256
[Josep speaking indistinctly]

15:23.256 --> 15:25.175
[Karal]
Leave.

15:26.926 --> 15:28.553
There a problem, ke?

15:28.553 --> 15:31.681
No.
We just need some privacy.

15:50.075 --> 15:52.369
The Chetzemoka
has not changed course.

15:52.369 --> 15:54.204
Even if Naomi is alive,

15:54.204 --> 15:56.831
looks like she doesn't have
control of the ship.

15:56.831 --> 15:59.125
That may not last long.

15:59.125 --> 16:01.002
Drummer said Naomi
was the smartest person

16:01.002 --> 16:02.545
she ever know.

16:02.545 --> 16:04.005
[softly]
Pashang-fong!

16:04.005 --> 16:07.133
Drummer will insist
that we go see for ourself.

16:07.133 --> 16:09.511
You're not going to
tell her?

16:11.262 --> 16:12.847
She's my ankawala.

16:12.847 --> 16:14.933
I cannot keep something
like this from her.

16:14.933 --> 16:17.268
She not the only one
you love here.

16:17.268 --> 16:19.604
♪ ♪

16:19.604 --> 16:21.981
Marco knows the situation.

16:21.981 --> 16:24.401
He will send us orders.

16:24.401 --> 16:25.985
And when he does,

16:25.985 --> 16:28.488
you and yours
will follow them.

16:28.488 --> 16:30.365
If it happen
any other way,

16:30.365 --> 16:33.952
what come after
will be your fault.

16:33.952 --> 16:37.288
So you will keep
your silence.

16:37.288 --> 16:38.707
Understood?

16:38.707 --> 16:40.625
Understood.

16:40.625 --> 16:44.921
♪ ♪

16:44.921 --> 16:47.924
[silverware and dishes
clinking]

16:54.013 --> 16:55.598
[Erich]
You should get a plate

16:55.598 --> 16:57.183
before these animals
finish it off.

16:57.183 --> 16:59.185
[Hutch] Rich people eat good.
[Erich] Ha.

16:59.185 --> 17:00.353
[cook]
It's not fancy.

17:00.353 --> 17:02.355
There's not much left
in the house.

17:02.355 --> 17:04.691
We appreciate
the hospitality.

17:04.691 --> 17:06.276
Any luck?

17:06.276 --> 17:08.403
- Reactor won't start.
[Amos] She got enough fuel.

17:08.403 --> 17:09.571
But something's trippin'

17:09.571 --> 17:11.322
every time we try
to start the bottle.

17:11.322 --> 17:12.949
The house batteries
are dead.

17:12.949 --> 17:14.826
There's no backup
generator.

17:14.826 --> 17:18.037
With no power, this island's
gonna get pretty cold.

17:18.037 --> 17:21.040
[porter] Food here's not gonna
last much longer either.

17:23.752 --> 17:25.336
Not that you're not
all welcome

17:25.336 --> 17:28.590
to as much you'd like,
of course.

17:28.590 --> 17:31.009
Should we be seeing how far
south the chopper can get

17:31.009 --> 17:32.677
before it runs out of fuel?

17:32.677 --> 17:34.095
[Amos]
Not yet.

17:34.095 --> 17:36.055
Whatever's causing
the reactor shutdown,

17:36.055 --> 17:37.932
it has to be mechanical,
electrical, or software.

17:37.932 --> 17:39.350
[Erich] Oh.

17:39.350 --> 17:41.853
That just means there could be
one of anything that exists.

17:41.853 --> 17:44.105
Peaches and I can handle
the mechanical and electrical,

17:44.105 --> 17:45.648
but I'm no debugger.

17:45.648 --> 17:47.609
If it's a computer problem,
we're gonna need some help.

17:47.609 --> 17:49.319
Could be a security protocol,

17:49.319 --> 17:51.446
some kind of kill switch
you missed.

17:51.446 --> 17:54.115
If you can convince the ship
that we're its rightful owner,

17:54.115 --> 17:55.492
that'd be fuckin' helpful.

17:55.492 --> 17:57.285
Yeah, okay.

17:57.285 --> 17:59.662
You can fake an ID
like that?

18:02.540 --> 18:04.542
[electronic chirping]

18:08.087 --> 18:09.088
Fuck.

18:15.678 --> 18:17.639
Hold it right there.

18:17.639 --> 18:19.808
Are you
with relief services?

18:19.808 --> 18:22.018
[Amos] No.
- Well, we saw your helicopter.

18:22.018 --> 18:24.062
We've been waiting
for evacuation for weeks.

18:24.062 --> 18:26.272
We're running low on supplies.

18:26.272 --> 18:28.900
We're not here to evacuate you
or give you anything,

18:28.900 --> 18:30.068
so fuck off!

18:30.068 --> 18:31.820
You have to help us,
please!

18:31.820 --> 18:33.613
They're just
more off-season staff.

18:33.613 --> 18:34.948
They're no threat.

18:34.948 --> 18:37.158
We've had no communication
since the rocks hit.

18:37.158 --> 18:39.327
I mean, none of the houses
have power now.

18:39.327 --> 18:40.286
We need food.

18:40.286 --> 18:42.080
That's not
our fuckin' problem.

18:42.080 --> 18:43.915
We're not a part
of any relief effort.

18:43.915 --> 18:45.333
Sorry.

18:45.333 --> 18:47.460
[overlapping entreaties]
- Then what are you doing here?

18:47.460 --> 18:48.878
[woman]
Please.

18:48.878 --> 18:50.713
We're trying to fix
the shuttle in that hangar

18:50.713 --> 18:53.424
and take it up to Luna.

18:53.424 --> 18:55.218
You guys
are welcome to come.

18:55.218 --> 18:57.428
[Erich scoffs]
What the fuck?

18:59.013 --> 19:00.431
- It's a small ship.

19:00.431 --> 19:02.892
- It'll be uncomfortable,
but it's a short ride.

19:02.892 --> 19:04.644
No one else
is gonna help them,

19:04.644 --> 19:06.938
certainly not the people
that own these houses.

19:06.938 --> 19:08.773
Are we gonna tell everybody
on the fuckin' island

19:08.773 --> 19:10.942
- what our plans are?
- He's not wrong.

19:10.942 --> 19:13.152
This isn't the thing
you want to spread around.

19:13.152 --> 19:15.572
You want my help
fixing that ship?

19:15.572 --> 19:18.616
We don't leave anyone behind
who wants to come.

19:18.616 --> 19:20.493
[Erich] Fine.
We'll do it ourselves.

19:20.493 --> 19:22.912
Stay here if you want,
princess.

19:26.708 --> 19:28.793
Anyone wants to leave
better be at this hanger

19:28.793 --> 19:30.420
by the time the ship is ready.

19:30.420 --> 19:32.505
We're not waiting.

19:32.505 --> 19:34.173
You understand?

19:34.173 --> 19:36.634
- [excited murmuring, laughter]
[Clarissa] Follow me.

19:36.634 --> 19:38.845
[Amos] Shut up.
[Clarissa] Let's go inside.

19:43.266 --> 19:44.392
Your ships will rendezvous

19:44.392 --> 19:45.852
with the Serrio Mal
and the Koto,

19:45.852 --> 19:47.687
and together,
you will intercept

19:47.687 --> 19:49.647
and engage the Rocinante.

19:49.647 --> 19:52.317
Destroying it is your first

19:52.317 --> 19:54.986
and only priority.

19:54.986 --> 19:56.905
Make sure it is done.

19:58.114 --> 19:59.824
Good hunting.

20:02.493 --> 20:04.162
Tenye wa chesh gut!

20:04.162 --> 20:05.455
[weakly]
Tenye wa chesh gut.

20:09.667 --> 20:11.669
You have your orders.

20:12.879 --> 20:15.757
- They make no sense.
- That's not for you to say.

20:15.757 --> 20:18.927
You said that the Rocinante
was burning to a trap.

20:18.927 --> 20:20.845
If that's true,

20:20.845 --> 20:23.348
why pick the fight?

20:23.348 --> 20:25.516
So that the Free Navy
can be seen killing

20:25.516 --> 20:28.770
a symbol of assimilation
and compromise...

20:28.770 --> 20:30.605
the thing
that has kept the Belt

20:30.605 --> 20:33.149
on the Inners' leash
for generations.

20:33.149 --> 20:36.194
Only a fool
would believe that.

20:36.194 --> 20:39.614
And you are many things,
but you are not a fool.

20:42.116 --> 20:45.244
You pledged your loyalty
and the lives of your faction

20:45.244 --> 20:48.081
to Marco Inaros.

20:48.081 --> 20:50.583
You withdrawing that, ke?

20:50.583 --> 20:53.586
[tense music]

20:53.586 --> 20:56.965
♪ ♪

20:56.965 --> 20:58.633
No.

20:58.633 --> 21:00.718
If it needs to be done,

21:00.718 --> 21:02.470
we will do it.

21:02.470 --> 21:06.224
♪ ♪

21:06.224 --> 21:07.934
As well you should.

21:09.686 --> 21:12.271
Ready the Dewalt.

21:12.271 --> 21:15.525
I need a tight-beam
to the Serrio Mal,

21:15.525 --> 21:18.528
- then the Koto.
[Bertold] Oye, bosmang.

21:20.571 --> 21:22.490
[beeping]

21:22.490 --> 21:24.409
[softly]
Give me your gun.

21:26.661 --> 21:29.205
- Why?
- You know why.

21:29.205 --> 21:31.582
♪ ♪

21:31.582 --> 21:34.002
There's no need.

21:34.002 --> 21:36.087
Then there's no reason
not to.

21:36.087 --> 21:38.256
♪ ♪

21:38.256 --> 21:41.676
Camina, please.
Do this for me.

21:41.676 --> 21:48.683
♪ ♪

21:58.234 --> 22:01.237
[quiet music]

22:01.237 --> 22:08.244
♪ ♪

22:22.592 --> 22:24.302
[chime]

22:32.977 --> 22:36.022
[stirring music]

22:36.022 --> 22:43.029
♪ ♪

22:57.585 --> 22:59.712
My condolences.

22:59.712 --> 23:01.047
Thank you.

23:03.049 --> 23:05.885
You came here
to say something, so say it.

23:05.885 --> 23:08.471
Three more cabinet ministers
just resigned.

23:08.471 --> 23:10.890
A no-confidence vote is being
scheduled for tomorrow.

23:10.890 --> 23:13.601
- Paster's gonna lose.
- Snap elections, then.

23:13.601 --> 23:15.937
Yes, but those are
unpredictable.

23:15.937 --> 23:18.981
A lot of people feel it's
too risky in times like these.

23:18.981 --> 23:21.150
- You're talking about a coup.
- What?

23:21.150 --> 23:23.361
- That's treason.
- No, ma'am.

23:23.361 --> 23:25.113
The ministers just thought
it would come across

23:25.113 --> 23:27.949
as more impartial
if I were the one to ask.

23:27.949 --> 23:29.575
Madam Avasarala,

23:29.575 --> 23:31.869
if you were nominated
to lead us again,

23:31.869 --> 23:33.329
would you serve?

23:44.841 --> 23:48.094
Oh, my God.
They picked you.

23:48.094 --> 23:52.181
Mostly for the name
recognition, I think.

23:52.181 --> 23:55.434
The once and future queen.

23:55.434 --> 23:57.270
Congratulations.

23:57.270 --> 23:59.438
I'd like you
in my cabinet.

23:59.438 --> 24:02.650
[laughing]

24:02.650 --> 24:04.652
I'm serious.

24:04.652 --> 24:07.280
I trust you, and you're
not afraid of me.

24:09.699 --> 24:12.410
I'm transferring
to a strike group.

24:12.410 --> 24:14.954
Hopefully the one that
takes out Inaros himself.

24:14.954 --> 24:18.916
Felix, you haven't served
on a combat ship for 20 years.

24:18.916 --> 24:20.168
You have a history

24:20.168 --> 24:22.253
of driving military people
away from you.

24:22.253 --> 24:23.796
Inaros has ships.

24:23.796 --> 24:26.048
He has millions of rocks
he could drop.

24:26.048 --> 24:28.384
He has the protomolecule.

24:28.384 --> 24:31.971
If you go toe-to-toe
with him, we could lose.

24:31.971 --> 24:34.891
I need your help.

24:34.891 --> 24:38.352
Someone's going to kill
Marco Inaros,

24:38.352 --> 24:41.230
and I'd really like
for it to be me.

24:50.907 --> 24:53.201
A Belter, a Martian,

24:53.201 --> 24:55.453
and an Earther go to a bar.

24:55.453 --> 24:56.537
[laughing]

24:56.537 --> 24:57.872
The Belter says,

24:57.872 --> 25:01.834
"Give me a shot of your
finest Martian whiskey.

25:01.834 --> 25:05.588
Drinking like my enemy
helps me think like my enemy."

25:05.588 --> 25:07.673
The Martian says,
"Give me a shot

25:07.673 --> 25:10.760
of your finest Earth tequila.

25:10.760 --> 25:12.887
Drinking like my enemy

25:12.887 --> 25:16.807
helps me think like my enemy."

25:16.807 --> 25:20.144
You never finished it.

25:20.144 --> 25:22.855
The Earther says,
"Give me a shot

25:22.855 --> 25:25.483
of the finest Belter
liquor you have.

25:25.483 --> 25:27.526
Best the Belt has to offer."

25:27.526 --> 25:28.861
The bartender says,

25:28.861 --> 25:31.030
"Because it helps you
think like your enemy?"

25:31.030 --> 25:32.615
And the Earther says, "No,

25:32.615 --> 25:34.242
because I'm trying
to drink less.

25:34.242 --> 25:36.786
The best the Belt
has to offer is terrible."

25:42.333 --> 25:43.918
It used to be funnier.

25:46.045 --> 25:48.256
[glasses clink]

26:02.228 --> 26:03.980
[soft beep]

26:03.980 --> 26:05.690
How does this look?

26:05.690 --> 26:07.566
[Clarissa]
It's green up here.

26:07.566 --> 26:09.402
- Same as last time.
- All right.

26:09.402 --> 26:11.153
Let's try it again.

26:11.153 --> 26:13.823
Erich, run the magnetic
bottle test.

26:17.660 --> 26:19.495
Peaches, he asleep up there?

26:19.495 --> 26:21.372
[Clarissa] He's not here.
He just stepped out.

26:21.372 --> 26:23.249
God damn it.

26:23.249 --> 26:24.875
[softly]
Fuck.

26:24.875 --> 26:28.254
[beeping]

26:29.964 --> 26:34.719
[Erich] Timmy. Outside now.
We got trouble.

26:34.719 --> 26:36.304
[Pinkwater leader]
You all must be pretty cold.

26:36.304 --> 26:39.056
The power grid is down
all across the island.

26:39.056 --> 26:42.351
Hopefully it'll be back up
and running in a few days.

26:42.351 --> 26:44.437
Hello. I'm in charge
of private security

26:44.437 --> 26:46.564
- for Winnipesaukee Island.
[Erich] Chief rent-a-cop.

26:46.564 --> 26:50.067
[scoffs] I was just telling
your friends here

26:50.067 --> 26:51.694
that we hope to have
communication with the mainland

26:51.694 --> 26:53.237
back up and running shortly.

26:53.237 --> 26:54.530
They want all our food.

26:54.530 --> 26:56.073
And in the meantime,

26:56.073 --> 26:58.326
we believe it's best to have
all food and other supplies

26:58.326 --> 27:01.787
moved to a central location
for efficient distribution.

27:01.787 --> 27:03.205
Fine.

27:03.205 --> 27:05.750
- Bring it all here.
- We'll keep an eye on it.

27:05.750 --> 27:07.293
My team's already set up
a temporary base of operations

27:07.293 --> 27:08.627
in one of the houses.

27:08.627 --> 27:12.006
We feel it's the best location
to secure vital supplies.

27:12.006 --> 27:13.632
So you're taking
someone's house.

27:13.632 --> 27:15.634
Now you want to take
everyone's food, too?

27:15.634 --> 27:17.720
[Erich] This is
the most pathetic shakedown

27:17.720 --> 27:18.929
I've ever seen.

27:18.929 --> 27:21.515
[scoffs]
You must be new at this.

27:23.893 --> 27:26.645
I understand you came here
in a helicopter.

27:26.645 --> 27:29.065
My people will need access
to that as well.

27:29.065 --> 27:30.608
[Hutch]
I've got a better idea.

27:30.608 --> 27:33.569
Why don't you blow me,
rent-boy?

27:33.569 --> 27:35.488
No one here
is giving you anything.

27:35.488 --> 27:37.531
Well, if you think
I'm being unreasonable,

27:37.531 --> 27:39.408
you can complain
to the authorities.

27:39.408 --> 27:42.370
Oh, right.
There are no authorities now.

27:42.370 --> 27:43.621
Except for me.

27:43.621 --> 27:45.873
So why don't you
shut the fuck up

27:45.873 --> 27:47.708
and do what
I told you to do?

27:47.708 --> 27:49.960
I don't think I will.

27:49.960 --> 27:52.254
[guns cock]

27:53.422 --> 27:55.508
Is that why you're here?

27:55.508 --> 27:57.051
For that old shuttle?

27:57.051 --> 27:59.053
We were told
it didn't work.

27:59.053 --> 28:01.097
[whistles]

28:03.140 --> 28:05.017
[Clarissa]
Stop it!

28:05.017 --> 28:07.019
[Erich]
Get out of the way.

28:07.019 --> 28:09.563
We don't have to do this.

28:09.563 --> 28:11.565
We were in Baltimore.

28:11.565 --> 28:13.651
They're burying people
in mass graves along the road.

28:13.651 --> 28:17.405
Please, just
put down your guns.

28:17.405 --> 28:20.408
[suspenseful music]

28:20.408 --> 28:24.245
♪ ♪

28:24.245 --> 28:26.038
Just walk away.

28:26.038 --> 28:29.667
♪ ♪

28:29.667 --> 28:33.587
Just walk
the fuck away.

28:33.587 --> 28:40.052
♪ ♪

28:54.150 --> 28:58.028
You know
they'll be back, right?

28:58.028 --> 29:00.614
Enough people have died
for no reason.

29:00.614 --> 29:02.741
Why are we waiting for them
to give us a reason?

29:02.741 --> 29:04.452
It's a pretty stupid
strategy.

29:04.452 --> 29:06.203
All right.
Let's get back to work

29:06.203 --> 29:08.664
so we'll be gone
before they come back.

29:08.664 --> 29:11.667
[dramatic music]

29:11.667 --> 29:18.674
♪ ♪

29:21.510 --> 29:24.513
[hydraulics hissing]

29:26.682 --> 29:30.728
I don't understand why Marco
wants us to take this risk.

29:30.728 --> 29:33.147
It's five ships
against one.

29:33.147 --> 29:35.441
We won't lose.

29:35.441 --> 29:38.319
Now he's got you
keeping secrets from me, too.

29:38.319 --> 29:41.614
You know something.

29:41.614 --> 29:45.826
Don't lie.
You're not good at it.

29:45.826 --> 29:47.786
If I'm holding
something back,

29:47.786 --> 29:50.206
is it so unthinkable
that I have a good reason?

29:50.206 --> 29:52.041
Don't treat me
like a child.

29:52.041 --> 29:54.335
I've earned the truth.

29:54.335 --> 29:56.504
Marco killed Klaes Ashford,

29:56.504 --> 29:58.923
and I sat on my hands
and played nice with him

29:58.923 --> 30:00.841
so you would be safe.

30:00.841 --> 30:02.885
He killed a woman I loved,

30:02.885 --> 30:06.096
and now he wants me and mine
to murder her friends.

30:06.096 --> 30:08.098
And I go along again.

30:08.098 --> 30:09.850
How much shit do I have to eat

30:09.850 --> 30:12.436
before you treat me
with some respect?

30:12.436 --> 30:15.439
[dramatic music]

30:15.439 --> 30:18.859
♪ ♪

30:18.859 --> 30:20.069
[beep]

30:20.069 --> 30:26.951
♪ ♪

30:26.951 --> 30:30.496
Do you love us, too?

30:30.496 --> 30:31.997
What?

30:33.624 --> 30:36.669
You loved Naomi.

30:36.669 --> 30:38.587
Do you love us?

30:38.587 --> 30:40.631
Of course.

30:41.924 --> 30:45.302
Do we mean as much to you
as she did?

30:45.302 --> 30:48.222
♪ ♪

30:48.222 --> 30:50.015
I need to
hear you say it.

30:50.015 --> 30:52.935
♪ ♪

30:52.935 --> 30:54.979
Yes.

30:54.979 --> 31:01.860
♪ ♪

31:01.860 --> 31:05.573
It's possible
that Naomi is still alive

31:05.573 --> 31:07.700
on that ship.

31:07.700 --> 31:11.078
Marco wants us to kill
Rocinante

31:11.078 --> 31:13.539
before they can help her.

31:13.539 --> 31:16.166
You can't save her.

31:16.166 --> 31:19.920
You know what happens when
someone goes against Marco.

31:19.920 --> 31:22.506
If we are disloyal now,

31:22.506 --> 31:25.843
we'll be killed,
not just you, not just me,

31:25.843 --> 31:27.595
but all of us.

31:27.595 --> 31:32.683
♪ ♪

31:32.683 --> 31:35.060
I beg you to respect that.

31:35.060 --> 31:38.188
♪ ♪

31:38.188 --> 31:40.190
[sighs]

31:40.190 --> 31:42.735
♪ ♪

31:42.735 --> 31:44.737
[beeping]

31:44.737 --> 31:51.744
♪ ♪

32:03.339 --> 32:05.049
All finished?

32:05.049 --> 32:07.509
As far as I can tell.

32:07.509 --> 32:09.928
Electrical system's
intact, anyway.

32:09.928 --> 32:11.138
You?

32:11.138 --> 32:13.223
Timmy's now the registered
owner of the ship.

32:13.223 --> 32:16.143
There's no hidden kill switches
on startup.

32:16.143 --> 32:18.979
This operating system
is old...

32:18.979 --> 32:20.731
but functional.

32:20.731 --> 32:24.693
- If only the ship would start.
- Yeah. That would be nice.

32:26.236 --> 32:29.365
[sighs]

32:29.365 --> 32:31.408
He calls you Peaches.

32:31.408 --> 32:32.660
Yeah.

32:32.660 --> 32:34.286
- Why?
- I don't know.

32:36.330 --> 32:38.290
Why do you call him Timmy?

32:38.290 --> 32:40.501
Because that's his name.

32:42.753 --> 32:44.463
Should I ask?

32:45.881 --> 32:47.800
I wouldn't.

32:49.802 --> 32:52.805
[beeping]

32:52.805 --> 32:56.684
[indistinct chatter]

32:56.684 --> 32:58.727
[Erich] If you want to run
another power cycle,

32:58.727 --> 33:00.312
I'm ready to.

33:00.312 --> 33:02.690
I'm taking a fuckin' break.

33:08.362 --> 33:11.031
It's not going well?

33:11.031 --> 33:13.033
I don't see anyone
standing watch.

33:13.033 --> 33:16.495
It's quiet. Relax.

33:16.495 --> 33:17.871
You!

33:17.871 --> 33:20.290
Quit fucking around
and get up on that roof.

33:20.290 --> 33:22.209
Keep an eye
on the tree line.

33:22.209 --> 33:23.627
[Theo] Who the fuck
are you ordering around

33:23.627 --> 33:26.422
- right now, old man?
[Hutch] Shut up and do it.

33:26.422 --> 33:28.298
[Theo] I'll come
find you later.

33:28.298 --> 33:30.300
Hey, get inside.

33:30.300 --> 33:32.594
We'll let you know
when it's safe.

33:32.594 --> 33:34.304
You her dad?

33:34.304 --> 33:35.931
She's distracting him.

33:35.931 --> 33:37.891
He can get laid
in his own time.

33:37.891 --> 33:39.935
You keep pushing my guys,
they're gonna push back.

33:39.935 --> 33:41.311
I don't want you
killing any of them.

33:41.311 --> 33:42.646
We can all hug
and make up

33:42.646 --> 33:44.314
when we get
out of this fuckin' planet.

33:44.314 --> 33:45.649
Okay.

33:45.649 --> 33:48.777
[sighs]
Opened the liquor cabinet.

33:50.446 --> 33:53.073
With a rock.

33:53.073 --> 33:54.575
Thanks.

33:58.036 --> 33:59.955
Ohh.

33:59.955 --> 34:02.583
[breathes deeply]

34:02.583 --> 34:05.127
I guess last time you left,
you were happy to go.

34:06.712 --> 34:08.547
Not at first.

34:08.547 --> 34:11.633
What changed?

34:11.633 --> 34:13.927
I found my place.

34:13.927 --> 34:15.846
Great.

34:22.227 --> 34:25.731
I spent my whole life learning
how to survive in Baltimore.

34:27.232 --> 34:28.984
Just a street crook,
I guess, but...

34:28.984 --> 34:31.987
[sniffs]
...I understood it.

34:31.987 --> 34:34.948
Now it's all gone.

34:34.948 --> 34:37.201
I remember
thinking that.

34:39.703 --> 34:41.789
I don't want to leave
everything behind

34:41.789 --> 34:43.373
and start all over again.

34:45.501 --> 34:47.795
Ahh.
I remember thinking that, too.

34:47.795 --> 34:49.171
[sniffs]
Yeah.

34:49.171 --> 34:51.590
But you know what coming
back to Baltimore's taught me?

34:51.590 --> 34:53.008
What?

34:53.008 --> 34:55.385
No one starts over

34:55.385 --> 34:58.430
'cause no one really
leaves anything behind.

35:04.645 --> 35:06.647
[exhales deeply]

35:08.899 --> 35:10.317
Shit.

35:11.652 --> 35:13.862
It's the power couple.

35:15.989 --> 35:17.324
[Hutch]
What?

35:19.076 --> 35:21.370
It was right in front
of me the whole time.

35:21.370 --> 35:23.121
Sometimes you got to stop
thinking about something

35:23.121 --> 35:26.041
to figure it out.

35:26.041 --> 35:28.043
Even if we do get
everything up and running,

35:28.043 --> 35:30.587
who knows if this old boat
has enough thrust to lift off

35:30.587 --> 35:33.090
with every damn person
on the island inside?

35:33.090 --> 35:35.801
We're just growing
the tribe.

35:35.801 --> 35:36.927
What?

35:36.927 --> 35:38.887
Amos says
that humans are tribal,

35:38.887 --> 35:41.557
and that when things get bad,
the tribe shrinks.

35:41.557 --> 35:43.517
That's how it works.

35:43.517 --> 35:45.978
- You should listen to him.
- I did.

35:45.978 --> 35:47.938
And he's right.

35:47.938 --> 35:49.940
But he's also wrong.

35:49.940 --> 35:52.651
On the road, he said
we were a tribe of two.

35:52.651 --> 35:55.279
But if we hadn't teamed up
with you guys,

35:55.279 --> 35:56.405
we'd be dead now.

35:56.405 --> 35:59.074
We were stronger
'cause our tribe grew.

35:59.074 --> 36:00.868
I'm still not sure
what your collection

36:00.868 --> 36:03.787
of scullery maids and butlers
is adding to the team.

36:03.787 --> 36:05.455
Does it matter?

36:05.455 --> 36:08.959
Maybe just being people
who need help is enough.

36:08.959 --> 36:12.170
If we decided to include
everyone in our tribe

36:12.170 --> 36:15.299
without demanding
that they prove we need them,

36:15.299 --> 36:17.509
maybe people wouldn't have
thrown rocks at us

36:17.509 --> 36:19.052
in the first place.

36:19.052 --> 36:21.096
[laughs]
Oh, Jesus Christ.

36:21.096 --> 36:23.390
Where did Timmy find you?

36:24.975 --> 36:28.478
Serving a life sentence
for multiple homicides.

36:30.772 --> 36:32.316
[device beeps]
[Amos] We got it.

36:32.316 --> 36:34.234
Bad power coupling
was tripping all the power

36:34.234 --> 36:35.694
when it got the juice.

36:35.694 --> 36:37.487
I yanked it and ran a bypass.

36:37.487 --> 36:40.490
Hopefully the extra load
won't set the ship on fire.

36:40.490 --> 36:42.075
Hold on.
I'm testing it now.

36:42.075 --> 36:44.912
[beeping]

36:44.912 --> 36:46.663
[beeps, power-up thrum]

36:46.663 --> 36:48.540
It fucking worked!

36:48.540 --> 36:50.083
Okay, I'll secure
everything down here.

36:50.083 --> 36:51.418
You guys do pre-launch.

36:51.418 --> 36:52.461
Let's get the fuck
out of here.

36:52.461 --> 36:53.712
[electronic voice]
Systems check.

36:53.712 --> 36:55.005
We're leaving in 15.

36:55.005 --> 36:57.925
Anyone who's not on the ship
is getting left behind.

36:57.925 --> 37:00.928
[suspenseful music]

37:00.928 --> 37:06.934
♪ ♪

37:08.518 --> 37:10.896
Come on, come on.
Let's go.

37:13.440 --> 37:15.901
[Amos] What's the holdup?
Let's move!

37:15.901 --> 37:18.904
[Hutch] We've got trouble.
Theo, what do you see?

37:18.904 --> 37:21.448
[Theo] Definitely
moving around in the trees.

37:21.448 --> 37:23.659
No clear line of...
[gunshot]

37:23.659 --> 37:24.993
Sniper!

37:24.993 --> 37:27.454
- Everyone find cover!
- Over there, return fire!

37:27.454 --> 37:28.997
[Amos]
Get the fuck down!

37:28.997 --> 37:32.834
[gunfire]

37:32.834 --> 37:33.877
Aah!

37:33.877 --> 37:40.884
♪ ♪

37:45.889 --> 37:47.349
Aah!

37:50.143 --> 37:52.479
Yaaaaah!

37:52.479 --> 37:55.315
Everyone find a seat.
Strap in if you can.

37:55.315 --> 37:57.150
Take everyone into the shuttle.

37:57.150 --> 37:59.152
Come on, let's go.

37:59.152 --> 38:04.950
♪ ♪

38:04.950 --> 38:06.243
[grunts]

38:06.243 --> 38:08.120
Thank you.
- [glass shatters]

38:08.120 --> 38:10.038
[man] Lay flat
on the deck if you have to.

38:10.038 --> 38:13.000
You might black out
when we lift off.

38:13.000 --> 38:14.418
[metallic clank]

38:14.418 --> 38:16.003
[Pinkwater crewman]
Kill the light cycle

38:16.003 --> 38:18.338
and shoot anyone
who resists!

38:20.590 --> 38:22.676
We're going now!

38:24.052 --> 38:25.303
[Erich]
Aah!

38:25.303 --> 38:28.056
[Amos]
Go, move, move!

38:29.016 --> 38:32.019
[gunshots]

38:32.019 --> 38:35.480
♪ ♪

38:35.480 --> 38:37.315
[Erich]
Come on!

38:37.315 --> 38:38.608
[Amos]
Move, move!

38:38.608 --> 38:40.193
[grunts]

38:40.193 --> 38:42.612
[Amos] Go!
[Hutch] Leave him! He's done!

38:42.612 --> 38:44.948
[gunfire continues]

38:44.948 --> 38:51.955
♪ ♪

39:08.430 --> 39:10.265
[Hutch]
Aah!

39:10.265 --> 39:12.350
[Amos]
Fall back! Fall back!

39:12.350 --> 39:14.102
Go!

39:14.102 --> 39:18.440
[gunfire continues]

39:18.440 --> 39:20.609
[Hutch] They're fighting
on both sides.

39:22.736 --> 39:24.321
Aah!

39:26.698 --> 39:28.658
I got you!

39:28.658 --> 39:32.412
♪ ♪

39:32.412 --> 39:35.332
[gunfire continues]

39:35.332 --> 39:37.209
[Hutch] You good?
- I'm good! Go!

39:37.209 --> 39:39.461
Go!

39:39.461 --> 39:41.463
[grunting]

39:41.463 --> 39:45.509
♪ ♪

39:45.509 --> 39:46.802
Aah!

39:46.802 --> 39:51.056
♪ ♪

39:51.056 --> 39:52.808
[thud, crash]

39:52.808 --> 39:54.392
Erich!

39:54.392 --> 39:56.103
Go!

39:56.103 --> 39:59.106
[screaming]

40:02.609 --> 40:05.028
[Hutch] She killed them all!
With her bare hands.

40:05.028 --> 40:08.031
[Erich] I'm gonna be a lot
nicer to her from now on.

40:08.031 --> 40:09.825
[Hutch]
Clear!

40:09.825 --> 40:12.828
[Amos grunts]

40:12.828 --> 40:14.955
Get her inside.
Finish pre-flight.

40:14.955 --> 40:16.581
[gunfire]

40:16.581 --> 40:20.210
[Clarissa]
I'm not leaving you behind.

40:20.210 --> 40:21.503
[gunfire]

40:21.503 --> 40:24.506
[bullets ricocheting]

40:24.506 --> 40:31.513
♪ ♪

40:36.852 --> 40:39.396
It's gettin' hot!

40:39.396 --> 40:41.731
[buzzer blaring]

40:41.731 --> 40:43.942
Come on, let's go!

40:45.694 --> 40:48.029
- [blaring continues]
- We got to go!

40:48.029 --> 40:51.825
[power-up thrumming]

40:51.825 --> 40:58.832
♪ ♪

40:58.832 --> 41:00.333
[gun clicks]

41:00.333 --> 41:02.210
- [gunshot]
- Aah!

41:02.210 --> 41:05.422
[Hutch] Amos!
- Ah!

41:05.422 --> 41:06.715
Aah!

41:06.715 --> 41:10.093
[both groaning]

41:11.720 --> 41:14.389
[Hutch]
Aaaah!

41:14.389 --> 41:21.396
♪ ♪

41:23.148 --> 41:24.941
Punch it!

41:26.776 --> 41:30.989
[beeping]

41:30.989 --> 41:33.617
[electronic voice]
Initiating launch.

41:33.617 --> 41:36.077
Please wait until hangar doors
are fully open.

41:36.077 --> 41:37.996
Fuck this!

41:48.423 --> 41:51.426
[groaning]

42:18.370 --> 42:21.414
[quiet music]

42:21.414 --> 42:23.416
♪ ♪

42:23.416 --> 42:26.419
[object clinking]

42:33.301 --> 42:35.804
[hissing]

42:43.853 --> 42:46.773
[hissing]

42:46.773 --> 42:49.776
[dramatic music]

42:49.776 --> 42:56.783
♪ ♪

43:24.936 --> 43:27.939
[soft emotional music]

43:27.939 --> 43:34.946
♪ ♪

43:48.877 --> 43:51.379
May I come in?

43:51.379 --> 43:53.423
Of course.

43:59.346 --> 44:01.348
[beep]

44:06.770 --> 44:09.105
You've been keeping
to yourself.

44:09.105 --> 44:11.483
I didn't think
you wanted to see me.

44:12.942 --> 44:14.778
To be honest...

44:16.988 --> 44:18.782
...I didn't.

44:25.663 --> 44:27.165
- I'm sorry.
- I'm sorry.

44:30.919 --> 44:32.921
You have nothing
to be sorry for.

44:32.921 --> 44:35.507
- I wish that were true.
- No.

44:35.507 --> 44:38.093
I brought Naomi here

44:38.093 --> 44:41.137
because I thought...

44:43.807 --> 44:45.767
And now she's gone.

44:50.897 --> 44:53.274
And Cyn is dead.

44:54.651 --> 44:56.069
And all because of me...

44:56.069 --> 44:59.114
She's alive.

45:00.949 --> 45:02.534
What?

45:02.534 --> 45:05.328
Your mother is alive.

45:08.039 --> 45:09.791
But...

45:09.791 --> 45:13.545
I saw her outside
with no suit.

45:13.545 --> 45:17.173
S-she somehow managed
to make a hard vacuum transit

45:17.173 --> 45:20.260
to the Chetzemoka
before it got under way.

45:20.260 --> 45:23.888
She's aboard it now.

45:23.888 --> 45:27.183
She didn't walk
into that airlock

45:27.183 --> 45:30.103
out of sadness or despair

45:30.103 --> 45:32.105
or remorse.

45:34.149 --> 45:37.235
She wasn't trying
to kill herself.

45:38.319 --> 45:41.406
She was trying to escape.

45:48.413 --> 45:51.458
[heavy music]

45:51.458 --> 45:57.964
♪ ♪

45:57.964 --> 46:00.049
She left us.

46:00.049 --> 46:07.056
♪ ♪

46:07.056 --> 46:09.517
She left us both...

46:11.394 --> 46:13.271
...again.

46:14.731 --> 46:16.232
No!

46:16.232 --> 46:17.901
No!

46:17.901 --> 46:20.111
[crying]
No.

46:32.832 --> 46:36.085
[crying]

46:36.085 --> 46:38.421
No.

47:02.862 --> 47:04.864
[soft whir, chirp]

47:24.050 --> 47:27.470
[dramatic music]

47:27.470 --> 47:34.477
♪ ♪

47:36.437 --> 47:39.983
[laughing]

47:46.072 --> 47:51.536
♪ ♪

47:51.536 --> 47:54.539
You asshole!

47:54.539 --> 47:59.252
[sobbing softly]

47:59.252 --> 48:03.172
[mumbling]

48:03.172 --> 48:10.179
♪ ♪

48:47.216 --> 48:50.219
[stirring music]

48:50.219 --> 48:57.226
♪ ♪

49:06.778 --> 49:10.907
[breathes deeply]

49:10.907 --> 49:13.910
[intense music]

49:13.910 --> 49:20.917
♪ ♪

49:28.966 --> 49:31.969
[metallic clanking]

49:33.888 --> 49:35.223
[clank]

49:36.933 --> 49:38.476
[clank]

49:40.937 --> 49:43.940
[light dramatic music]

49:43.940 --> 49:50.947
♪ ♪
